revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tpRstpEnable.name: tpRstpEnable
tpRstpEnable.description: Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol. 0. disable 1. enable

tpMstpEnable.name: tpMstpEnable
tpMstpEnable.description: Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol. 0. disable 1. enable

tpStpCistPriority.name: tpStpCistPriority
tpStpCistPriority.description: Enter a value from 0 to 61440 to specify the priority of the switch for comparison in the CIST. CIST priority is an important criterion on determining the root bridge. In the same condition, the switch with the highest priority will be chosen as the root bridge. The lower value has the higher priority. The value could be devided exactly by 4096.

tpStpHelloTime.name: tpStpHelloTime
tpStpHelloTime.description: Enter a value from 1 to 10 in seconds to specify the interval to send BPDU packets. It is used to test the links. (tpStpHelloTime+1)*2<=tpStpAgingTime.

tpStpAgingTime.name: tpStpAgingTime
tpStpAgingTime.description: Enter a value from 6 to 40 in seconds to specify the maximum time the switch can wait without receiving a BPDU before attempting to reconfigure. (tpStpHelloTime+1)*2<=tpStpAgingTime.

tpStpForwardDelay.name: tpStpForwardDelay
tpStpForwardDelay.description: Enter a value from 4 to 30 in seconds to specify the time for the port to transit its state after the network topology is changed. stpAgingTime<=(stpForwardDelay-1)*2.

tpStpHoldCount.name: tpStpHoldCount
tpStpHoldCount.description: Enter a value from 1 to 20 to set the maximum number of BPDU packets transmitted per Hello Time interval.

tpStpMaxHops.name: tpStpMaxHops
tpStpMaxHops.description: Enter a value from 1 to 40 to set the maximum number of hops that occur in a specific region before the BPDU is discarded.

tpStpPortConfigTable.name: tpStpPortConfigTable
tpStpPortConfigTable.description: Here you can configure the parameters of the ports for comparison in the CIST and the common parameters of all Instances. And you can view the status of the ports in the CIST. CIST (Common and Internal Spanning Tree) is the spanning tree in a switched network, connecting all devices in the network.

tpStpPortConfigEntry.name: tpStpPortConfigEntry
tpStpPortConfigEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of a port.

tpStpPortNumber.name: tpStpPortNumber
tpStpPortNumber.description: Displays the port number of the switch.

tpStpPortEnable.name: tpStpPortEnable
tpStpPortEnable.description: Select Enable /Disable STP function for the desired port. 0. Disable 1. Enable 2. ErrPort

tpStpPortPriority.name: tpStpPortPriority
tpStpPortPriority.description: Enter a value from 0 to 240 divisible by 16. Port priority is an important criterion on determining the root port. In the same condition, the port with the highest priority will be chosen as the root port. The lower value has the higher priority.

tpStpPortExPathCost.name: tpStpPortExPathCost
tpStpPortExPathCost.description: ExPath Cost is used to choose the path and calculate the path costs of ports in different MST regions. It is an important criterion on determining the root port. The lower value has the higher priority. automatic when value is zero. Make sure that Path Cost ranges from 0 to 2000000.

tpStpPortInPathCost.name: tpStpPortInPathCost
tpStpPortInPathCost.description: InPath Cost is used to choose the path and calculate the path costs of ports in an MST region. It is an important criterion on determining the root port. The lower value has the higher priority. Make sure that Path Cost ranges from 0 to 2000000.

tpStpEdgePortStatus.name: tpStpEdgePortStatus
tpStpEdgePortStatus.description: Select Enable/Disable Edge Port. The edge port can transit its state from blocking to forwarding rapidly without waiting for forward delay. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpStpPointToPointStatus.name: tpStpPointToPointStatus
tpStpPointToPointStatus.description: Select the P2P link status. If the two ports in the P2P link are root port or designated port, they can transit their states to forwarding rapidly to reduce the unnecessary forward delay. 0. auto 1. force enable 2. force disable

tpStpPortMCheck.name: tpStpPortMCheck
tpStpPortMCheck.description: Select Enable to perform MCheck operation on the port. Unchange means no MCheck operation. 0. unChange 1. enable

tpStpPortStpVersion.name: tpStpPortStpVersion
tpStpPortStpVersion.description: Displays the STP version of the port. 1. stp 2. rstp 3. mstp

tpStpPortRole.name: tpStpPortRole
tpStpPortRole.description: Displays the role of the port played in the STP Instance. 1.Disable:Indicates the port that is not participating in the STP. 2.Alternate:Indicates the port that can be a backup port of a root or master port. 3.Backup:Indicates the port that is the backup port of a designated port. 4.Designated:Indicates the port that forwards packets to a downstream network segment or switch. 5.root:Indicates the port that has the lowest path cost from this bridge to the Root Bridge and forwards packets to the root. 6.Master:Indicates the port that connects a MST region to the common root. The path from the master port to the common root is the shortest path between this MST region and the common root.

tpStpPortStatus.name: tpStpPortStatus
tpStpPortStatus.description: Displays the working status of the port. 1.Disconnected: In this status the port is not participating in the STP. 2.Blocking: In this status the port can only receive BPDU packets. 3.Learning: In this status the port can receive/send BPDU packets and learn MAC address. 4.Forwarding: In this status the port can receive/forward data, receive/send BPDU packets as well as learn MAC address.

tpStpPortLag.name: tpStpPortLag
tpStpPortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

tpMstpRegionName.name: tpMstpRegionName
tpMstpRegionName.description: Create a name for MST region identification using up to 32 characters.

tpMstpRevision.name: tpMstpRevision
tpMstpRevision.description: Enter the revision from 0 to 65535 for MST region identification.

tpMstpInstanceConfigTable.name: tpMstpInstanceConfigTable
tpMstpInstanceConfigTable.description: Here you can set the VLAN-to-spanning-tree mapping configuration.

tpMstpInstanceConfigEntry.name: tpMstpInstanceConfigEntry
tpMstpInstanceConfigEntry.description: An entry contains of the mstp instance.

tpMstpInstanceId.name: tpMstpInstanceId
tpMstpInstanceId.description: Displays Instance ID of the switch,0 representative CIST.

tpMstpInstanceEnable.name: tpMstpInstanceEnable
tpMstpInstanceEnable.description: Displays status of the instance. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpMstpInstancePriority.name: tpMstpInstancePriority
tpMstpInstancePriority.description: Enter the priority of the switch in the instance. It is an important criterion on determining if the switch will be chosen as the root bridge in the specific instance.Make sure that Priority ranges from 0 to 61440 and could be divided exactly by 4096

tpMstpInstanceVlanId.name: tpMstpInstanceVlanId
tpMstpInstanceVlanId.description: Enter the desired VLAN ID. After modification here, the new VLAN ID will be added to the corresponding instance ID and the previous VLAN ID won't be replaced.The format of input VLAN ID shoud be like '1,3,4-7,11-30' in the range from 1 to 4094.

tpMstpClearInstanceVlanId.name: tpMstpClearInstanceVlanId
tpMstpClearInstanceVlanId.description: This object use to clear instance's vlan id.The cleared VLAN ID will be automatically mapped to the CIST.

tpMstpInstancePortConfigTable.name: tpMstpInstancePortConfigTable
tpMstpInstancePortConfigTable.description: A port can play different roles in different spanning tree instance. Here you can configure the parameters of the ports in different instance IDs as well as view status of the ports in the specified instance.

tpMstpInstancePortConfigEntry.name: tpMstpInstancePortConfigEntry
tpMstpInstancePortConfigEntry.description: An entry contains of the mstp instance port config.

tpMstpInstancePortConfigId.name: tpMstpInstancePortConfigId
tpMstpInstancePortConfigId.description: The instance ID for its port configuration, 1-8.

tpMstpInstancePortNumber.name: tpMstpInstancePortNumber
tpMstpInstancePortNumber.description: Displays the port number of the switch.

tpMstpInstancePortPriority.name: tpMstpInstancePortPriority
tpMstpInstancePortPriority.description: Enter the priority of the port in the instance. It is an important criterion on determining if the port will be chosen as the root port by the device connected to this port.

tpMstpInstancePortPathCost.name: tpMstpInstancePortPathCost
tpMstpInstancePortPathCost.description: Path Cost is used to choose the path and calculate the path costs of ports in an MST region. It is an important criterion on determining the root port. The lower value has the higher priority.

tpMstpInstancePortRole.name: tpMstpInstancePortRole
tpMstpInstancePortRole.description: Displays the role of the port played in the STP Instance. 1. Disable 2. Alternate 3. Backup 4. Designated 5. root 6. Master

tpMstpInstancePortStatus.name: tpMstpInstancePortStatus
tpMstpInstancePortStatus.description: Displays the working status of the port. 1. Disable 2. Blocking 3. Learning 4. Forwarding

tpMstpInstancePortLag.name: tpMstpInstancePortLag
tpMstpInstancePortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

tpStpPortDefendTable.name: tpStpPortDefendTable
tpStpPortDefendTable.description: Port defend function is to prevent the devices from any malicious attack against STP features..

tpStpPortDefendEntry.name: tpStpPortDefendEntry
tpStpPortDefendEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of a port protection.

tpStpDefendPortNumber.name: tpStpDefendPortNumber
tpStpDefendPortNumber.description: Displays the port number of the switch.

tpStpLoopDefendEnable.name: tpStpLoopDefendEnable
tpStpLoopDefendEnable.description: Loop defend is to prevent the loops in the network brought by recalculating STP because of link failures and network congestions. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpStpRootBridgeDefendEnable.name: tpStpRootBridgeDefendEnable
tpStpRootBridgeDefendEnable.description: Root defend is to prevent wrong network topology change caused by the role change of the current legal root bridge. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpStpTcDefendEnable.name: tpStpTcDefendEnable
tpStpTcDefendEnable.description: TC defend is to prevent the decrease of the performance and stability of the switch brought by continuously removing MAC address entries upon receiving TC-BPDUs in the STP network. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpStpBPDUDefendEnable.name: tpStpBPDUDefendEnable
tpStpBPDUDefendEnable.description: BPDU defend is to prevent BPDUs flood in the STP network. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpStpDefendPortLag.name: tpStpDefendPortLag
tpStpDefendPortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

tpStpTcDefendThreshold.name: tpStpTcDefendThreshold
tpStpTcDefendThreshold.description: Enter a number from 1 to 100. It is the maximum number of the TC-BPDUs received by the switch in a TC Protect Cycle.

tpStpTcDefendTimer.name: tpStpTcDefendTimer
tpStpTcDefendTimer.description: Enter a value from 1 to 10 to specify the TC Protect Cycle.

tpMstpTopologyChange.name: tpMstpTopologyChange
tpMstpTopologyChange.description: The topology of spanning tree has changed.
